vestments would withdraw its shareholder proposal before rims annual meeting on january   rim announced that its ceos balsillie and lazaridis had stepped down from their positions they were replaced by thorsten heins heins hired investment banks rbc capital markets and jp morgan to seek out potential buyers interested in rim while also redoubling efforts on releasing blackberry  on march   rim announced a strategic review of its future business strategy that included a plan to refocus on the enterprise business and leverage on its leading position in the enterprise space heins noted we believe that blackberry cannot succeed if we tried to be everybodys darling and all things to all people therefore we plan to build on our strength balsillie resigned from the board of directors in march  while lazaridis remained on the board as vice chairman following the assumption of role as ceo heins made substantial changes to the companys leadership team changes included the departures of chief technology officer david yach chief operating officer jim rowan senior vice president of software alan brenner chief legal officer karima bawa and chief information officer robin bienfait following the leadership changes heins hired kristian tear to assume the role of chief operating officer frank boulben to fill the chief marketing officer role and appointed dan dodge the ceo of qnx to take over as chief technology officer on july   steven e zipperstein was appointed as the new vice president and chief legal officer on march   lazardis relinquished his position as vice chairman and announced his resignation from the board of directors later in the year heins was replaced by john s chen who assumed the ceo role in the first week of november chens compensation package mainly consists of blackberry shares—a total of  million—and he will be entitled to the entire amount of shares after he has served the company for five years heins received an exit package of  million chen has a reputation as a turnaround ceo turning the struggling enterprise software and services organization sybase into enough of a success to sign a merger with sap in  chen was open about his plans for blackberry upon joining the company announcing his intent to move away from hardware manufacturing to focus on enterprise software such as qnx blackberry uem and athoc he has firm views on net neutrality and lawful access and has been described by former colleagues as a quick thinker who holds people accountable workforce reductionsedit in june  rim announced its prediction that q  revenue would drop for the first time in nine years and also unveiled plans to reduce its workforce in july  the company cut  jobs the biggest layoff in its history and the first major layoff since november   when the company laid off  of its workforce  employees the layoff reduced the workforce by around  from  employees to  on june   the company announced a planned workforce reduction of  by the end of its fiscal  as part of a  billion cost savings initiative on july    employees from blackberrys research and development department and new product testing were laid off the layoffs were part of the turnaround efforts on september   blackberry confirmed that the company will have a massive layoff of  employees by the end of  this would be approximately  percent of the companys workforce blackberry had at its peak about  employees but when ceo john chen joined blackberry in  there were additional layoffs in february  to compete with smartphones so the total employees numbered  on july   blackberry announced an additional layoff of an unspecified number of employees with another  laid off in february  stock fluctuationsedit in june  rim stock fell to its lowest point since  on december   rim shares fell to their lowest price since january  overall in  the share price tumbled  percent from january to december causing its market capitalization to fall below book value by march  shares were worth less than  from 