sage blackberry os javaedit the existing javabased blackberry os was intended to operate under much different simpler conditions such as low powered devices narrow network bandwidth and high security enterprises however as the needs of the mobile user evolved the aging platform struggled with emerging trends like mobile web browsing consumer applications multimedia and touch screen interfaces users could experience performance issues usability problems and instability the company tried to enhance the aging platform with a better web browser faster performance a bundled application store and various touch screen enhancements but ultimately decided to build a new platform with qnx at its core while most other operating systems are monolithic—the malfunction of one area would cause the whole system to crash – qnx is more stable because it uses independent building blocks or kernels preventing a domino effect if one kernel breaks rims final major os release before the release of blackberry  was blackberry  which was often criticized as dated and referred to as a temporary stopgap blackberry tablet os qnxedit the blackberry playbook was the first rim product whose blackberry tablet os was built on qnx launched in april  as an alternative to the apple ipad however it was criticized for having incomplete software it initially lacked native email calendaring and contacts and a poor app selection it fared poorly until prices were substantially reduced like most other tablet computers released that year android tablets such as the motorola xoom and samsung galaxy tab and the hp touchpad the blackberry tablet os received a major update in february  as well as numerous minor updates blackberry  qnxedit main article blackberry  blackberry  a substantially updated version of blackberry tablet os intended for the next generation blackberry smartphones was originally planned for release in early  the company delayed the product several times remembering the criticism faced by the blackberry playbook launch and citing the need for it to be perfect in order to stand a chance in the market the most recent model with this os was the classic which was introduced in december  and was discontinued in early july  androidedit main articles blackberry priv and blackberry dtek in september  blackberry announced the priv a handset running android  lollipop and compatible with an upgrade to android marshmallow it is the first phone by the company not to run an inhouse built operating system blackberrys android is almost stock android with their own tweaks to improve productivity and security blackberry has implemented some of the features of blackberry  within android like blackberry hub blackberry virtual keyboard blackberry calendar blackberry contacts app etc on april   blackberry reported that it sold  phones in its fiscal fourth quarter amid expectations of – handset sales for the first full quarter of reporting since the privs release on july   a new midrange model with only an onscreen keyboard was introduced the unusually slim blackberry dtek powered by the latest version of android  marshmallow and featuring a inch full highdefinition display blackberry chief security officer david kleidermacher stressed data security during the launch indicating that this model included builtin malware protection and encryption of all user information by then the blackberry classic which used the blackberry  os had been discontinued in july  industry observers expected the company to announce two additional smartphones over the subsequent  months presumably also with the android os however blackberry coo marty beard told bloomberg that the company’s never said that we would not build another bb device at mwc barcelona  tcl announced the blackberry keyone the keyone is the last phone designed inhouse by blackberry acquisitionsedit through the years particularly as the company evolved towards its new platform blackberry has made numerous acquisitions of third party companies and technology slipstream data incedit slipstream data inc was a network optimization  data compression  network acceleration software company blackberry acquired the company as a wholly owned subsidiary on july   the company continues to operate out of waterloo certicomedit certicom corp is a cryptography company founded in  by gordon agnew ron mullin and scott vanstone the certicom intellectual property portfolio includes over  patents and patents pending worldwide that cover key aspects of elliptic curve cryptography ecc software optimizations efficient hardware implementations methods to enhance the security and various cryptographic protocolscitation needed the national security agency nsa has licensed  of certicoms ecc patents as a way of clearing the way for the implementation of elliptic curves to protect us and allied government information certicoms current customers include general dynamics motorola oracle research in motion and unisyscitation needed on january   verisign entered into an agreement to acquire certicom research in motion put in a counteroffer which was deemed superior verisign did not match this offer and so certicom announced an agreement to be acquired by rim upon the completion of this transaction certicom became a wholly owned subsidiary of rim and was delisted from the toronto stock exchange on march   dash navigationedit in june  rim announced they would acquire dash navigation makers of the dash express torch mobileedit in august  rim acquired torch mobile developer of iris browser enabling the inclusion of a webkitbased browser on their blackberry devices which became the web browser in subsequent java based operating systems blackberry  blackberry  and operating systems qnx based blackberry tablet os and blackberry  the first product to contain this browser the blackberry torch  was named after the company datavizedit on september   dataviz inc sold their office suite documents to go and other assets to research in moti