gins developing products for mobitex wireless packetswitched data communications networks often used by military and police forces firefighters and ambulance services rim releases the digisync film keykode reader a product for the motion picture industry jim balsillie joins rim he would become coceo along with lazaridis rim releases the interctive pager also known as the rim  its first keyboardbased device rim goes public on the toronto stock exchange the rim  a dramatically slimmed down twoway pager is released the stock symbol rimm is added to nasdaq rim announces it has received fcc approval in the us to begin selling its first blackberry device the  with mobile email rim adds voice calling capabilities to the blackberry  rim is added to the nasdaq  releases its first blackberry with a colour screen rim marks its th anniversary announcing it has passed the onemillion subscriber mark by year’s end it has more than two million subscribers using its devices rim hits four million subscribers balsillie and lazaridis are named among time magazine’s  most influential people blackberry releases the first in a line of consumerfriendly pearl devices adding a digital camera and multimedia capabilities rim becomes the most valuable company on the tsx with a market capitalization surpassing  billion the company has  million subscribers and introduces the first of its curve blackberrys but rim is caught flatfooted by the overwhelming response to apple’s new iphone rim stock hits a high of  in june but the euphoria is short lived the stock market crash in september takes its shares below  and its first touchscreen blackberry the storm is critically panned as iphone hype grows with the new g model blackberry launches its app world marketplace to compete with apple’s app store its selection pales in comparison a problem that is never solved rim surpasses  million users and announces it has shipped its  millionth smartphone it buys ottawabased qnx software systems which would help reshape its operating system software going forward a few months after the first ipad hits the market rim unveils its playbook tablet but says it won’t be released until early the following year an unpolished playbook is finally released in the spring later than expected and reviews are not kind a few months later the company announces it’s cutting  jobs in october users around the world suffer through a fourday service outage lazaridis and balsillie step down as coceos and are replaced by thorsten heins balsillie also resigns from the board of directors within months heins announces  layoffs and a delay to the critical blackberry  software update which is seen as the company’s last chance to stay alive the stock touches a low of  in the fall heins finally unveils blackberry  and the first two smartphones to use the operating system the z and q the company purchases a super bowl ad to build hype for the new company which officially changes its name to blackberry the phones don’t sell well enough to bolster its fortunes lazaridis steps down as vice chairman and leaves the board of directors in august the company says it is open to “strategic alternatives” including a possible sale on friday the company announced it was laying off another  employees and planned to refocus on the enterprise market on monday it announced fairfax financial holdings offered to buy the company in a deal worth about us billion   shaw media report an error blackberry fairfax jim balsillie mike lazaridis prem watsa research in motion thorsten heins waterloo wireless editors picks politics as the canada child benefit turns  who has actually benefited politics new documents on trudeaus bahamas trip raise fresh questions on longrunning ethics investigation canada government revokes groups charity status audit cites possible funding of pakistani militants canada after blowing july  deadline canada seems likely to legalize pot while ignoring un treaties canada reality check will closing tax looph