the nsas national information assurance partnership or niap which reviews commercial technology products to see if they meet enhanced security standards for government use niap has also endorsed tools from blackberry rivals that outplayed blackberry in consumer smartphones including apple inc and samsung electronics the fear that eavesdroppers are listening in to government communications has risen sharply in recent years with an unencrypted mobile phone call between a senior us state department officer and the us ambassador to ukraine intercepted and leaked online in early  the tools are based on technology from secusmart which blackberry acquired in  after the german startup won a contract to lock down chancellor angela merkels mobile phone in the wake of claims by a former us intelligence contractor that it was tapped by the nsa german prosecutors in  dropped an inquiry into claims that merkels phone was bugged saying they had not found enough evidence to continue the probe blackberry said its encrypted voice and text messaging products are used by government agencies in  countries in europe latin america southeast asia and africa germany is its biggest government customer related stories blackberry wins m in royalty dispute with qualcomm blackberry stops making phones to focus on software security   thomsonreuters all rights reserved click here to comment on this article close  more ways to share stumbled linkedin vine reddit delicious newstrust tell my politician technocrati short url email article comment contact print     a   a    like our page share share thewire blackberry ltd won the right to sell the us government secure messaging tools for encrypting phone calls and text messages garnering an endorsement from the national security agency for the products blackberry us government messaging  friday  jul   am  around the web powered by newsmax join the newsmax community register to comment login to comment please review community guidelines before posting a